Bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a boil. Once boiling, add @Spinach and Ricotta Ravioli{9%ounce} and reduce heat to a simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until ravioli are al dente and floating to the top, ~{4-5%minutes}. Drain.

> Recipe suggestion (additional ingredients not included): Melt 1 TBSP butter in a large pan over medium-high heat. Whisk in ¼ cup sour cream (or cream cheese) and a few splashes of water until a smooth and creamy sauce forms. Add cooked ravioli and stir until coated. Stir in a pinch of chili flakes and a squeeze of lemon juice. Taste and season with salt and pepper.